{"title": "Unsanitized use of FileUpload filename", "summary": "  The unsanitized use of the filename provided by FileUpload could lead to path traversal attacks, since an attacker could manipulate the filename to gain access to unauthorized resources. Try to avoid referencing filenames that are open to such manipulation, or if it is unavoidable, ensure that the filename is sanitized and that appropriate validation measures are taken. ", "description": "\n\nThe unsanitized use of the filename provided by FileUpload could lead to path traversal attacks, since an attacker could manipulate the filename to gain access to unauthorized resources.\nTry to avoid referencing filenames that are open to such manipulation, or if it is unavoidable, ensure that the filename is sanitized and that appropriate validation measures are taken.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid wherever possible\n\n\u2705 Sanitize user input when resolving paths, for example by using `FilenameUtils.getName()` to normalize the path:\n\n```java\n  ServletFileUpload upload = new ServletFileUpload();\n  List<FileItem> fileItems = upload.parseRequest(request);\n\n  for (FileItem item : fileItems) {\n    String filename = FilenameUtils.getName(item.getName());\n    // ...\n  }\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-73"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/java_lang_file_upload_filename", "https://owasp.org/www-community/attacks/Path_Traversal"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}